Incase you wondered:<br>
Here are the scientific proves that Santa Clause doesn’t exist:<br>
<br>
For the first:<br>
No known reindeers can, what we know, fly – but there actually are 300000 unspecified living specimen that yet have been classified, and just because most of these are insects and other small animals, that does not mean that there ARE NOT flying reindeers which only Santa have seen….<br>
<br>
For the second:<br>
There a 2 billion children (under eighteen) in the world- but since Santa don’t seem to care for Muslim-, Jude-, Hindi- and buddies- children; this is reduced to 15% of the total children population, as according to Swedish statistic Yearbook is estimated to 321 million children.<br>
<br>
In average there’s approximate 3,5 children/home, which give us that there’s about 91,8 million homes for these children. And to make the calculation easier, lets say there’s at least 1 child that’s been good during the year/household.<br>
<br>
Thanks to different time zones Santa has a 31-hour workday. This only if he travels west, which seems more logical. From this we get he will have to do 822,6 visits/second! If one specify this a little more Santa has to, in 1 thousand of a second, park the carriage, jump off, climb down the chimney, fill the stockings with gifts, put rest under the Christmas tree, eat up all the food every family left for him, climb up the chimney, sit down in the carriage and drive to next home.<br>
<br>
If all the 91,8 millions homes would be spread out even across the globe (to make the calc. easier) we’re talking about 1.26 Km/household, which gives Santa Clause a total travel of 115 millions Km and we have not even taken into consideration those times during the day most living organisms do at least once a day, eating, do his needs etc. etc.<br>
<br>
WITH this and an simple equation one could calculate that Santa’s carriage are traveling with the mere speed of 1050 Km/sec, i.e. Mach 3000. <br>
Just to compare, the fastest vehicle made by humans was the space shuttle Odysseus, which traveled with the pity speed of 44.1 Km/sec. An ordinary average reindeer travels 0,0067 Km/sec.<br>
<br>
For the third:<br>
